Concord v0.3.0
Release Date: October 24, 2025
Status: Production Ready - Filesystem-Native Coordination Substrate

## Current Version: v0.3.0

### What's Working

Python SDK with Agent base class
File notifications (inotify/fsevents) with sub-2ms latency
Mount abstraction layer with standardized directory structure
Optional FUSE filesystem layer
Content-addressable storage (CAS) bus with atomic writes
Multi-agent orchestration with PlanExecutor
Exactly-once semantics (rename + tombstones)
Append-only event logs (O_APPEND)
Policy enforcement (no_network, max_tokens)
Dependency management and template resolution
Comprehensive test suite (pytest)
Transport benchmarks (file 5.6ms, FIFO 1.3ms, UDS 0.13ms p50)
4-agent pipeline (50ms time-to-green, 100% reliability)
Complete 2x2 performance matrix (SLM + FUSE)
Atomic filesystem commit protocol (write-fsync-rename-dir_fsync)
Storage contract probe (C1-C3 validation)
LangGraph checkpoint saver integration
ConcordFS evaluation across 3,700+ experiments (see papers/)

### What's NOT Yet Implemented

Model router daemon
Remote agent coordination (SSH/9P)
Security sandboxing (cgroups/namespaces)
TLA+ formal specification
Production FUSE implementation (Rust-based)

